This paper is about Neural Machine Translation (NMT), which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and falls under the Computer Science category. The paper discusses the architecture hyperparameters of NMT, which involves deep learning techniques and optimization algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also involves extensive experimentation and analysis, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves image-to-text translation, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category.
